  "notes": [
    "Form 6251 (Alternative Minimum Tax \u2014 Individuals) widget map for the IRS-hosted TY2025 PDF. PDF /Title metadata is '2025 Form 6251'.",
    "Widget enumeration walks /Annots on each page (NOT reader.get_fields(), which over-reports non-terminal containers). Sorted into visual reading order (page asc, rect_top desc, rect_left asc) before correlation to line numbers.",
    "Page 1 carries lines 1a-11 (Part I AMTI plus Part II tentative-minimum-tax flow). Page 2 carries Part III lines 12-40, the alternative capital-gain-rate flow used ONLY when line 7 instructs the filer to use Part III.",
    "TY2025 constants embedded in the instructions but not on the form itself: exemption $88,100 (Single/HoH), $137,000 (MFJ/QSS), $68,500 (MFS); exemption phase-out threshold $626,350 (Single/HoH/MFS) and $1,252,700 (MFJ/QSS) with 25%-per-dollar recapture; 26%/28% breakpoint $239,100 ($119,550 MFS) with $4,782 ($2,391 MFS) adjustment.",
    "Layer 1 compute_form_6251_fields fills lines 1a-11 deterministically. Part III (lines 12-40) is ONLY populated when line 7 instructs \u2014 the common case is blank Part III.",
    "Layer 1 does NOT carry 'taxpayer_ssn' (Form 1040 holds the canonical SSN). The f1_2 widget is mapped here for completeness but the renderer leaves it empty."
